<font color="#FF0000">DEAR ABBY, PART II</font><br>
<tt>Mon Nov 17 20:09:34 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Anne;<br>
Real committment comes from trust, trusting ourselves to be ourselves with those we care about.<br><br>
When I first met my wife, I didn't want to committ myself for fear of being hurt. She could see that and one day, we as sat together at the table, she said to me;<br>
&quot;I have a friend that really loves this guy, but she's afraid that he may not be ready for a serious committment because of what his past has been like, what should I tell her.&quot;<br>
I answered;<br><br>
&quot;Well, I have a friend and he is not sure, his girlfriend would be ready for a serious commitment because of .....&quot;<br><br>
And so it went, by using a non-existent third party we were able to air out what was really bothering, comfusing or what we didn't understand about each other.<br><br>
We've now been married over 20 yerars.<br>

